---
import { LuExternalLink } from "react-icons/lu"
---

<section class="flex flex-col gap-y-6 print:gap-y-1" id="about">
  <div class="space-y-2">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold" id="about">About Me</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
    <div class="text-muted-foreground">
      I'm a Software Developer from Bangladesh. My journey into programming
      started during my undergraduate years with C, and if I'm being honest, it
      wasn't a great experience. I struggled to connect the concepts, and
      programming felt more like memorizing syntax than solving problems. Things
      only started to click during my second year when I picked up JavaScript
      and built a few simple web pages. Seeing the browser respond to the code I
      wrote made programming finally make sense.
    </div>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground">
      After graduating, I joined Zventures LLC as a Frontend Engineering Intern
      and was promoted to a full-time Frontend Developer six months later. Since
      then, I've been building production SaaS applications and learning that
      writing software goes far beyond implementing features. The more I worked
      on real products, the more I found myself thinking about maintainability,
      reusable systems, performance, and leaving a codebase easier for the next
      engineer to understand than I found it.
    </div>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground">
      Outside of work, I spend a lot of time reading documentation, building
      personal projects, and exploring technologies beyond my day-to-day
      responsibilities. Lately, that means learning backend development and
      experimenting with AI-assisted workflows. I use AI to explore ideas, speed
      up repetitive work, and understand unfamiliar technologies, but I still
      believe good software comes from thoughtful engineering decisions not
      blindly accepting generated code.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
